# 💳 Credit Card Approval Prediction System

## 📌 Project Overview

The Credit Card Approval Prediction System is a Machine Learning-based web application that predicts whether a credit card application is likely to be approved or rejected based on the applicant's financial and personal information. The project automates the credit card approval process, reducing manual effort and improving decision-making efficiency. It is developed using Python, Flask, Scikit-Learn, HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap.

## 🎯 Problem Statement

Banks and financial institutions receive thousands of credit card applications every day. Manually reviewing each application is time-consuming and prone to human errors. This project automates the approval process using machine learning algorithms by analyzing applicant details such as income, employment, education, family status, and financial information to predict approval or rejection.


## ✨ Features

- User-friendly web interface for entering applicant details.
- Real-time credit card approval prediction.
- Dashboard displaying project information and statistics.
- Machine learning model integrated with a Flask web application.
- Data preprocessing and feature encoding for improved prediction accuracy.
- Evaluation of multiple machine learning algorithms such as Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest, and XGBoost.
- Responsive design using Bootstrap.
- Easy to deploy and extend for future enhancements.

